A fatal accident occurred after a learner with a Mercedes Benz car crushed six siblings to death in Edo state.  Reports have it that the incident happened in Arue-Uromi, Esan-North East Local Government Area of the state. Eyewitnesses at the scene revealed that four girls and two boys said to be siblings, who were playing football were crushed when the driver made an attempt to dodge a pothole and swerved to the spot where the kids were playing. Following the tragic incident which provoked anger of the residents of the community, the road was immediately blocked and the Mercedes Benz was burnt. Edo State Sector Commander of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) Henry Benamaisia, confirmed the incident. See Photos: By Ijendu Iheaka Aba (Abia) - The Police Command in Abia has confirmed the arrest of a driver whose vehicle crushed a woman and her son to death on Friday evening in Aba. The Police Public Relations Officer in the state, SP Geoffrey Ogbonna said the driver was taken into… June 23, 2019 In "Metro" By Peter Okolie Onitsha (Anambra) - Two persons were confirmed dead on Thursday when an articulated truck crushed a tricycle in Onitsha, Anambra. Sector Commander of Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) in the state, Mr Kumapayi Ayodele, said the incident occurred at about 10.45 a.m. along Obodoukwu Road, off Onitsha-Owerri… July 25, 2019 In "Metro" One pupil was crushed and two others injured in a multiple auto crash at Ikota area of Ajah, Lagos on Monday, the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports. Spokesperson for the Police in Lagos, DSP Ngozi Braide, who confirmed the incident, said the child was crushed at about 8a.m.on her… November 18, 2013 In "News"